    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix protocol timer duration in OpenAirInterface 5G\n\n### Summary\nThe protocol timer duration in OpenAirInterface 5G was configured with incorrect duration violating 3GPP timing requirements. This was caused by an incorrect time comparison in the `get_sf_time` and `get_slot_time` functions where the code was comparing the full time value with just the microsecond portion.\n\nThis fix corrects the time comparison logic to properly handle microsecond wraparound scenarios, ensuring that protocol timers operate with correct durations that comply with 3GPP timing requirements.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/vnf/src/vnf_p7.c`: Fixed time comparison in `get_sf_time` and `get_slot_time` functions\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/pnf/src/pnf_p7.c`: Fixed time comparison in `get_sf_time` and `get_slot_time` functions\n\n### Reproduction\nThe issue manifests when running 5G NSA mode with specific timing configurations where protocol timers would have incorrect durations, leading to synchronization issues between the VNF and PNF components. The incorrect timer durations can be observed in the timing information logs where subframe and slot timing calculations are inaccurate.\n"
}